    • test

      default boolean test​(T next, T prev)
      Description copied from interface: BinaryPredicate
      For consistency's sake the first parameter 'next' should receive the new/next instance that will enter the test, while the param 'prev' the oldest/previous instance.

      This allows the 'fluid' execution of Object.equals(Object) / Object::equals where the first... being 'next' has a lower probability of being null while the second 'prev' will always be null on first usage. preventing a NullPointerException.
